 second half of the 19th century.<\/p>\n<p>Mykolaiv Regional Art Museum named after V.V. Vereshchagina, became one of the recognized centers of culture and aesthetic education in the city. <strong>Today, the museum&#8217;s collection includes up to eighteen thousand exhibits, which are a kind of artistic chronicle of Ukraine and many other countries.<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>In the halls there is an exhibition of works, which includes painting, sculpture, graphics and decorative and applied art.<\/p>\n<p><strong>Tasks of the project<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>Perform 3D digitization of museum exhibits within the framework of the &#8220;Art Museum Digital Collection&#8221; and &#8220;Art Museum Digital Collection: Porcelain&#8221; projects. The porcelain museum collection consists of dishes (cup, saucer, vase, saucer, plate, etc.) and figurines. These are products from the countries of Western Europe at the end of the 18th and 20th centuries. (Germany, Austria, France, England, Spain), Eastern Europe of the beginning of the 19th &#8211; mid-20th centuries. (Ukraine, Poland and Russia) and East Asia of the 20th century. (Japan and China).<\/p>\n<p><strong>Ways to complete the task<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>After talking with the customer, we decided to use photogrammetry technology, which makes it possible to obtain high detail and an authentic look of museum exhibits.<\/p>\n<p><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-4242\" src=\"https:\/\/virtual-cube.online\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/11\/aero3d-work-process-300x200.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"881\" height=\"587\" srcset=\"https:\/\/virtual-cube.online\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/11\/aero3d-work-process-300x200.jpg 300w, https:\/\/virtual-cube.online\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/11\/aero3d-work-process-1024x683.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/virtual-cube.online\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/11\/aero3d-work-process-768x512.jpg 768w, https:\/\/virtual-cube.online\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/11\/aero3d-work-process-1536x1024.jpg 